{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AddingComments"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/comment(_:)","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Comment"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/EnablingAndDisabling","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AddingTags","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AssociatingBugs","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/LimitingExecutionTime","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Parallelization"]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Adding comments to tests","modules":[{"name":"Testing"}],"roleHeading":"API Collection"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is often useful to add comments to code in order:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"to provide context or background information about the code’s purpose;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"to explain how complex code implemented; or"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"to include details which may be helpful when diagnosing issues.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Test code is no different and can benefit from explanatory code comments, but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"often test issues are shown in places where the source code of the test is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unavailable such as in continuous integration (CI) interfaces or in log files."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Seeing comments related to tests in these contexts can help diagnose issues more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"quickly. Comments can be added to test declarations and the testing library will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatically capture and show them when issues are recorded."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Adding-a-code-comment-to-a-test-automatically","type":"heading","text":"Adding a code comment to a test automatically"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The easiest way to include a comment on a test is by adding it as a regular","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Swift code comment placed immediately before the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute:"}]},{"code":["\/\/ Assumes the standard lunch menu includes a taco","@Test func lunchMenu() {","  let foodTruck = FoodTruck(","    menu: .lunch,","    ingredients: [.tortillas, .cheese]","  )","  #expect(foodTruck.menu.contains { $0 is Taco })","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The comment "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\/\/ Assumes the standard lunch menu includes a taco\""},{"text":" will be added","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the test.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following language comment styles are supported:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Syntax","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Style","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/\/ ..."}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Line comment","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/\/\/ ..."}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Documentation line comment"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/* ... *\/"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Block comment"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"\/** ... *\/","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Documentation block comment","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table"},{"level":3,"text":"Comment formatting","type":"heading","anchor":"Comment-formatting"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Test comments which are automatically added from source code comments preserve","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"their original formatting, including any prefixes like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/\/"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"\/**","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is because the whitespace and formatting of comments can be meaningful in some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"circumstances or aid in understanding the comment—for example, when a comment","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"includes an example code snippet or diagram."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Adding a comment to a test programmatically","type":"heading","anchor":"Adding-a-comment-to-a-test-programmatically","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more precise control over a comment’s content, comments can be added to a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test programmatically by explicitly specifying them as trait arguments to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Test","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute. Programmatically adding comments allows for more precise"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"control of the comments’ content or formatting. It can also help to reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"repetition by allowing developers to define comments in one place and reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","t